====Synonyms====
* {{sense|relief}} {{l|ja|安堵|tr=[[あんど]], ''[[ando]]''}}

====Compounds====
* {{l|ja|安心感|tr=[[あんしんかん]], ''[[anshinkan]]''}}: sense of security
* {{l|ja|安心決定|tr=[[あんしんけつじょう]], ''[[anshin ketsujō]]''; [[あんじんけつじょう]], ''[[anjin ketsujō]]''}}: {{qualifier|Buddhism}} chanting the name of Buddha with purity of heart and mind; firm belief; complete confidence in the future
* {{l|ja|安心決定鈔|tr=[[あんしんけつじょうしょう]], ''[[Anshin Ketsujō Shō]]''}}: {{qualifier|Buddhism}} a two-volume scripture in [[w:Pure Land Buddhism|Pure Land Buddhism]]
* {{l|ja|安心得道|tr=[[あんしんとくどう]], ''[[anshin tokudō]]''}}: {{qualifier|Buddhism}} achieving [[nirvana]] through [[equanimity]] of [[spirit]]
* {{l|ja|安心立命|tr=[[あんしんりつめい]], ''[[anshin ritsumei]]''; [[あんじんりゅうめい]], ''[[anjin ryūmei]]''; [[あんじんりゅうみょう]], ''[[anjin ryūmyō]]''}}: spiritual peace and enlightenment; keeping an unperturbed mind through faith
* {{l|ja|一安心|tr=[[ひとあんしん]], ''[[hitoanshin]]''}}: feeling of relief
* {{l|ja|不安心|tr=[[ふあんしん]], ''[[fuanshin]]''}}: uneasiness, uncertainty

====Idioms====
* {{l|ja|安心無き読経は田中の蝦蟇の如し|tr=[[あんしんなきどきょうはたなかのがまのごとし]], ''[[anshin naki dokyō wa tanaka no gama no gotoshi]]''}}: "a sutra recital without peace of mind is just like a toad in a paddy" → reciting the sutras without having the proper spiritual mindset is as meaningful as the croaking of a toad in a rice paddy

